♪ Got no trouble. ♪

24
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:52.374
♪♪

25
00:01:52.479 --> 00:01:55.381
♪ Walk on the water. ♪

26
00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:58.350
♪♪

27
00:01:58.452 --> 00:02:02.150
♪ Walk on the water. ♪♪

28
00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:07.692
- I'll be by the stream.

29
00:02:07.794 --> 00:02:08.693
ABIGAIL'S MOM:
Do not swim.

30
00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:09.795
- I won't.

31
00:02:10.831 --> 00:02:12.129
(goat bleats)

32
00:02:17.237 --> 00:02:19.763
(birds chirping)

33
00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.386
(fire crackling)

34
00:03:22.736 --> 00:03:24.295
- Yum. yum. yum.

35
00:03:26.373 --> 00:03:27.568
Yum. yum. yum. yum. yum.

36
00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:51.391
I'm sailing away.
whoo. whoo. whoo. whoo.

37
00:04:07.314 --> 00:04:08.748
Yum. yum. yum.

38
00:04:16.923 --> 00:04:18.357
(branch breaks)
(Abigail gasps)

39
00:04:19.526 --> 00:04:20.892
(receding footsteps)

40
00:04:22.796 --> 00:04:26.494
(Jesus humming)

41
00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:40.939
(Abigail gasps)

42
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:45.919
(crickets chirping)

43
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:50.856
(rubbing sounds)

44
00:05:05.705 --> 00:05:07.571
(blowing)

45
00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:28.722
(crickets chirping)

46
00:05:57.924 --> 00:06:00.826
ABIGAIL'S MOTHER: (sighs) And
Joanna just isn't doing better.

47
00:06:00.927 --> 00:06:02.038
which will mean.
she will have to see

48
00:06:02.062 --> 00:06:03.325
if they will give her space

49
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:04.910
to sell her headdresses
at the market.

50
00:06:04.965 --> 00:06:06.831
And even if they do.
which doesn't seem likely.

51
00:06:06.933 --> 00:06:09.459
because last time I was
at the market. it looked full.

52
00:06:09.569 --> 00:06:11.470
she has to find time
to make them.

53
00:06:11.571 --> 00:06:13.811
But she needs to focus her time
on helping him get better

54
00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:14.899
so he can return to work

55
00:06:15.008 --> 00:06:17.500
before they give his job
to someone else.

56
00:06:17.611 --> 00:06:20.581
(sighs)
She just seems so scared.

57
00:06:20.680 --> 00:06:21.824
Do you think you could stop
by tomorrow

58
00:06:21.848 --> 00:06:25.478
to see if she needs help
with anything?

59
00:06:25.585 --> 00:06:27.554
- Hmm?

60
00:06:27.654 --> 00:06:30.099
- Can you stop tomorrow to see
if she needs help with anything?

61
00:06:30.123 --> 00:06:31.386
- Joanna?

62
00:06:31.491 --> 00:06:32.550
- Mm-hmm.

63
00:06:32.659 --> 00:06:34.491
- I have to stay late myself.

64
00:06:34.594 --> 00:06:35.594
I don't have time to...

65
00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:39.730
I will see.

66
00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:41.131
- Thank you.

67
00:06:41.434 --> 00:06:43.096
It will mean so much to her.

68
00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:44.403
You know how she gets.

69
00:06:44.437 --> 00:06:45.437
- Hmm.

70
00:06:47.641 --> 00:06:50.907
- So. Abigail. how was your day?

71
00:06:51.011 --> 00:06:52.011
- It was fine.

72
00:06:52.045 --> 00:06:53.877
Can I play with Joshua tomorrow?

73
00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:55.024
- Only after you finish
your chores...

74
00:06:55.048 --> 00:06:56.949
- I know!
I will get it all done first.

75
00:06:57.050 --> 00:06:58.416
- Don't interrupt.

76
00:06:58.518 --> 00:07:02.080
- I'm sorry. but after
second meal. may I go?

77
00:07:02.188 --> 00:07:03.952
- I will ask his mother.

78
00:07:04.057 --> 00:07:06.026
And where will you go?

79
00:07:06.126 --> 00:07:09.995
- Um. just the field.
maybe the stream.

80
00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:11.394
- No swimming.

81
00:07:11.498 --> 00:07:13.057
- I know...
and chores first.

82
00:07:17.537 --> 00:07:20.063
- So. what time were you
going to go see Joanna tomorrow?

83
00:07:20.173 --> 00:07:22.093
I was thinking maybe
the evening would be better.

84
00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:41.126
(hard blow)

85
00:07:57.510 --> 00:08:04.713
♪♪

86
00:08:10.991 --> 00:08:12.459
(blows)

87
00:08:19.265 --> 00:08:21.666
- Blessed are You. Lord our God.

88
00:08:21.768 --> 00:08:23.134
King of the Universe.

89
00:08:23.236 --> 00:08:24.704
Who brings sleep to My eyes.

90
00:08:24.804 --> 00:08:27.572
ABIGAIL: And there was one tool
I've never seen before.

91
00:08:27.674 --> 00:08:28.972
I don't know what it's for.

92
00:08:29.075 --> 00:08:30.805
I think He was building stuff.

93
00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:31.809
I don't know.

94
00:08:31.911 --> 00:08:32.955
And there was some food. too.

95
00:08:32.979 --> 00:08:35.574
but even though I was hungry
I didn't take any.

96
00:08:35.682 --> 00:08:36.911
because that would be wrong.

97
00:08:37.017 --> 00:08:39.680
But maybe we could take
a little bit this time.

98
00:08:39.786 --> 00:08:40.786
What do you think?

99
00:08:40.887 --> 00:08:42.685
But I'm glad I didn't.

100
00:08:42.789 --> 00:08:44.033
because that's when the man
got there.

101
00:08:44.057 --> 00:08:45.491
Come on. go faster.

102
00:08:45.592 --> 00:08:46.651
- I'm trying. Abby.

103
00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:48.004
but your legs
are going too fast.

104
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:50.554
- If He comes this time.
should we say something to Him?

105
00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:52.256
I think if you're with me.
it's okay.

106
00:08:52.565 --> 00:08:54.693
I didn't see a sword
or anything like that.

107
00:08:54.801 --> 00:08:57.635
So I don't think He'll kill us;
He seemed nice.

108
00:08:57.737 --> 00:09:00.104
Do you have a sword.
just in case?

109
00:09:00.206 --> 00:09:01.868
Oh. we're almost there!
Here it is!

110
00:09:09.682 --> 00:09:11.082
- Blessed are you. Lord our God.

111
00:09:11.184 --> 00:09:12.277
King of the universe.

112
00:09:12.585 --> 00:09:14.986
Who gives forth bread
from this earth.

113
00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:28.033
And I pray that if there
are ever two children

114
00:09:28.134 --> 00:09:30.262
who come visit my home here.

115
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.214
that you will give them
the courage to say. "Shalom..."

116
00:09:32.238 --> 00:09:33.238
- Let's go.

117
00:09:33.273 --> 00:09:34.673
- Stay...
He's a good man.

118
00:09:34.774 --> 00:09:37.214
- so that they will know they do
not have to remain in hiding.

119
00:09:37.310 --> 00:09:38.209
- He's a good man. stay.

120
00:09:38.311 --> 00:09:39.210
- Amen.

121
00:09:39.312 --> 00:09:40.211
- We need to go.

122
00:09:40.313 --> 00:09:41.872
- Stay...
we are going to stay.

123
00:09:41.981 --> 00:09:43.279
(Jesus roaring)

124
00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:46.849
(giggling)

125
00:09:46.953 --> 00:09:48.945
- Pffftt!!

126
00:09:50.256 --> 00:09:52.088
What's that sound I hear?

127
00:09:52.192 --> 00:09:54.559
Sheep don't sound like that.

128
00:09:54.661 --> 00:09:56.027
(makes another strange noise)

129
00:09:56.129 --> 00:09:58.598
(giggling)

130
00:09:58.698 --> 00:10:01.634
No. that's definitely not sheep.

131
00:10:01.734 --> 00:10:03.726
Maybe a rooster?

132
00:10:03.837 --> 00:10:05.032
Greetings. children.

133
00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:09.742
You know. it is not safe for a
child to wander from their home.

134
00:10:09.843 --> 00:10:13.007
You never know
if there are bad men around.

135
00:10:13.113 --> 00:10:15.639
You are wise to bring
your friend this time.

136
00:10:15.782 --> 00:10:17.273
- Joshua.

137
00:10:17.383 --> 00:10:18.874
- Shalom. Joshua.

138
00:10:20.854 --> 00:10:23.323
I admire your bravery
to come here.

139
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:24.955
You are a good friend.

140
00:10:25.058 --> 00:10:27.960
Well. don't worry.
I'm not a bad man.

141
00:10:28.061 --> 00:10:29.324
- See? I knew it.

142
00:10:29.629 --> 00:10:30.773
- You are free to stay
for a bit.

143
00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:32.698
but I'm afraid
I have some work to do.

144
00:10:32.799 --> 00:10:33.892
- Okay.

145
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:35.960
- And thank you for not
taking any food yesterday.

146
00:10:41.107 --> 00:10:43.770
- See? I knew it.

147
00:10:43.877 --> 00:10:45.641
So. what are you doing here?

148
00:10:45.745 --> 00:10:46.838
- I'm visiting for a time.

149
00:10:46.946 --> 00:10:48.039
- Where are you from?

150
00:10:48.148 --> 00:10:49.207
- Nazareth.

151
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:50.374
- What is that wood for?

152
00:10:50.683 --> 00:10:51.742
- I'm building something.

153
00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:52.910
- Are you a carpenter?

154
00:10:53.019 --> 00:10:54.681
- Sometimes.
but I'm a craftsman.

155
00:10:54.787 --> 00:10:55.907
I build all kinds of things.

156
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:57.821
- So. why don't you
live in a house?

157
00:10:57.957 --> 00:10:59.050
- I travel a lot.

158
00:10:59.159 --> 00:11:00.957
- How do you make money?

159
00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:02.255
- Abby!

160
00:11:02.362 --> 00:11:04.228
- Just asking Him
how He makes money.

161
00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:05.821
- I know. you shouldn't.

162
00:11:05.932 --> 00:11:07.127
- It's okay.

163
00:11:07.233 --> 00:11:08.929
I don't make money
when I travel.

164
00:11:09.035 --> 00:11:10.731
So. for now. I build things.

165
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:12.381
and I trade them
for my food and clothing.

166
00:11:12.405 --> 00:11:13.668
- What is that?

167
00:11:13.773 --> 00:11:18.006
- Ah. this is going to be
a lock and key.

168
00:11:18.111 --> 00:11:20.637
- Joshua... ask Him questions.
He's nice.

169
00:11:20.747 --> 00:11:21.840
- No. thank you.

170
00:11:21.948 --> 00:11:23.917
- What else will you build?

171
00:11:24.017 --> 00:11:25.747
- Wealthy people
love decorations

172
00:11:25.852 --> 00:11:28.287
and toys for their children.

173
00:11:28.388 --> 00:11:30.186
- My family isn't wealthy.

174
00:11:32.792 --> 00:11:34.317
- Many times. that's better.

175
00:11:34.427 --> 00:11:35.759
- I don't know about that.

176
00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:37.228
(chuckles)

177
00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:38.330
- You will.

178
00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:42.892
- My mom made me this.

179
00:11:43.002 --> 00:11:45.198
- Oh. what's her name?

180
00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:46.796
- Sarah.

181
00:11:46.906 --> 00:11:48.875
- Very pretty.

182
00:11:48.975 --> 00:11:51.376
- Okay. time to go home.

183
00:11:51.477 --> 00:11:52.775
Bye.

184
00:11:53.846 --> 00:11:55.337
(receding footsteps)

185
00:11:57.750 --> 00:11:59.048
(chuckles)

186
00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:06.020
(sanding noise)

187
00:12:41.928 --> 00:12:43.157
- It is good.

188
00:12:52.305 --> 00:12:54.900
- Blessed are You. Lord our God.

189
00:12:55.008 --> 00:12:56.476
King of the Universe.

190
00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:58.335
Who brings sleep to My eyes.

191
00:12:58.444 --> 00:12:59.841
slumber to My...

192
00:12:59.946 --> 00:13:01.141
(Owl hoots)

193
00:13:01.247 --> 00:13:02.247
(babbling brook)

194
00:13:03.483 --> 00:13:05.816
- Just leave Him alone.

195
00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:07.250
- Is He dead?

196
00:13:07.353 --> 00:13:08.446
Shh.

197
00:13:14.861 --> 00:13:17.956
- Couldn't have waited
half an hour. eh?

198
00:13:18.064 --> 00:13:19.498
- Can we be around today?

199
00:13:19.799 --> 00:13:23.031
These are my other friends.
and Joshua again.

200
00:13:23.136 --> 00:13:26.038
- Shalom. Abigail's friends.
and Joshua again.

201
00:13:26.139 --> 00:13:27.300
- Shalom.

202
00:13:27.407 --> 00:13:28.500
- Shalom.

203
00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.300
- Can we be around today?

204
00:13:31.411 --> 00:13:35.109
- I suppose.
but I have some work to do.

205
00:13:35.214 --> 00:13:36.807
You might have to help.

206
00:13:39.952 --> 00:13:40.845
Good.

207
00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:42.922
(water splashing)

208
00:13:44.457 --> 00:13:47.393
- How much longer
are you going to stay here?

209
00:13:47.527 --> 00:13:50.520
- Until it is time for Me to go.

210
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:52.162
- When's that?

211
00:13:52.265 --> 00:13:54.791
- Well. I have some work
to do here.

212
00:13:54.901 --> 00:13:55.901
and some people to meet.

213
00:13:57.070 --> 00:13:58.538
And then I will know
the right time.

214
00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:00.067
- You seem nice.

215
00:14:00.173 --> 00:14:01.173
Are you dangerous?

216
00:14:02.175 --> 00:14:07.239
- Mm. maybe to some.

217
00:14:07.347 --> 00:14:10.078
But no. not to you.

218
00:14:10.183 --> 00:14:11.845
And I won't harm anyone.

219
00:14:11.951 --> 00:14:13.476
- Do you have friends?

220
00:14:13.586 --> 00:14:16.050
- A few. and more to come.

221
00:14:16.155 --> 00:14:18.420
- Abby said you travel a lot.

222
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:21.119
Do you have a house?

223
00:14:21.227 --> 00:14:23.128
- My Father provides
everything I need.

224
00:14:23.229 --> 00:14:24.390
- Is your father rich?

225
00:14:25.598 --> 00:14:27.157
(chuckles)

226
00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:29.497
- Did Abigail tell you
to ask me that?

227
00:14:29.635 --> 00:14:31.399
- No.

228
00:14:31.504 --> 00:14:33.564
- That is a question
for another time.

229
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:36.001
- What's your favorite food?

230
00:14:36.109 --> 00:14:38.101
- Oh. Joshua the Brave speaks.

231
00:14:39.612 --> 00:14:42.582
Hmm.
I like so many different foods.

232
00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:47.377
But I especially love bread.
for many reasons.

233
00:14:47.487 --> 00:14:49.581
How are those spoons
coming along. girls?

234
00:14:49.889 --> 00:14:50.584
Good?

235
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.153
- Good.

236
00:14:52.258 --> 00:14:53.157
- String. is it tight?

237
00:14:53.259 --> 00:14:54.158
- Yep.

238
00:14:54.260 --> 00:14:55.260
- Almost?

239
00:14:55.294 --> 00:14:56.387
- Almost.

240
00:14:56.496 --> 00:14:58.260
- Okay.

241
00:14:58.364 --> 00:15:02.028
So. tell me. do you all know
how to pray the Shema?

242
00:15:02.135 --> 00:15:03.296
- Yes.

243
00:15:03.403 --> 00:15:05.395
- Oh. I would love to hear it.

244
00:15:05.505 --> 00:15:06.505
You lead us.

245
00:15:08.141 --> 00:15:09.609
TOGETHER: Hear. Israel.

246
00:15:09.942 --> 00:15:11.570
The Lord is our God.

247
00:15:11.677 --> 00:15:13.976
The Lord is one.

248
00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:18.176
You shall love the Lord.
your God. with all your heart.

249
00:15:18.284 --> 00:15:22.380
all your soul.
and all your might.

250
00:15:22.488 --> 00:15:26.084
And it shall come to pass.
if you surely listen

251
00:15:26.192 --> 00:15:29.253
to the commandments
I command you today.

252
00:15:29.362 --> 00:15:33.493
that you may gather
in your grain. your wine.

253
00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:35.124
and your oil.

254
00:15:35.234 --> 00:15:38.898
and you will eat.
and you will be satisfied.

255
00:15:39.005 --> 00:15:41.474
I am the Lord your God

256
00:15:41.574 --> 00:15:46.672
who led you from the land
of Egypt to be a God to you.

257
00:15:46.979 --> 00:15:49.448
I am the Lord your God.

258
00:15:49.549 --> 00:15:50.573
Amen.

259
00:15:53.052 --> 00:15:54.577
- Beautiful.

260
00:15:54.687 --> 00:15:55.687
Very good.

261
00:15:57.390 --> 00:15:59.621
- So. why don't you have a home?

262
00:16:02.662 --> 00:16:05.222
- My home is many places.

263
00:16:05.331 --> 00:16:07.300
- Why?

264
00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:09.198
- Because I have
a much larger job

265
00:16:09.302 --> 00:16:12.101
than just being a craftsman
or a teacher.

266
00:16:12.205 --> 00:16:13.503
- You are a teacher. too?

267
00:16:13.606 --> 00:16:14.665
- I will be soon.

268
00:16:14.974 --> 00:16:16.465
- What other job?

269
00:16:16.576 --> 00:16:20.479
- Everyone has a much larger job
than just their trade.

270
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:23.072
And <i>you</i> are more
than just students.

271
00:16:23.182 --> 00:16:26.482
You are at school
to show love to one another.

272
00:16:26.586 --> 00:16:29.181
and to take God's Word.
and to share it.

273
00:16:29.288 --> 00:16:33.658
And at home.
to honor your father and mother.

274
00:16:33.759 --> 00:16:37.093
And most important.
from the law of Moses.

275
00:16:37.230 --> 00:16:38.323
to love Who?

276
00:16:38.431 --> 00:16:42.562
- The Lord your God.
with all your heart.

277
00:16:42.668 --> 00:16:45.638
- Very good. Joshua the Brave.

278
00:16:45.738 --> 00:16:49.402
So. I will be doing my work
in many places.

279
00:16:55.448 --> 00:16:57.974
- Or maybe He's the best builder
who ever lived.

280
00:16:58.084 --> 00:17:00.053
- Or maybe He's stronger
than Samson.

281
00:17:00.152 --> 00:17:02.331
- Maybe He's going to be our
new teacher at synagogue school.

282
00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.449
- I think He's maybe
a new prophet.

283
00:17:04.557 --> 00:17:06.492
and He'll show us
the Word of God.

284
00:17:06.592 --> 00:17:10.290
- No. there's no new prophets;
Rabbi Josiah said so.

285
00:17:10.396 --> 00:17:12.262
- But maybe He's a murderer.

286
00:17:12.365 --> 00:17:13.663
- He is not!

287
00:17:13.766 --> 00:17:15.598
- But maybe that's why
He's by Himself.

288
00:17:15.701 --> 00:17:17.067
He's running and hiding.

289
00:17:17.203 --> 00:17:19.243
- Yeah. and probably He's
pretending to be a builder

290
00:17:19.338 --> 00:17:20.533
so no one will know.

291
00:17:20.640 --> 00:17:21.733
- That's not true!

292
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:24.567
He's building stuff with us;
we're watching Him do it.

293
00:17:24.677 --> 00:17:27.647
- Yeah. He's smart.
so we should listen.

294
00:17:27.747 --> 00:17:29.739
- But maybe we're even
helping Him build weapons

295
00:17:30.049 --> 00:17:31.108
and we don't even know it?

296
00:17:31.217 --> 00:17:32.742
- No. He's a good man.

297
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:34.611
- I think so too.

298
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:38.521
- I like Him. I'm just saying.
maybe He's a criminal.

299
00:17:38.624 --> 00:17:40.559
- But no matter what.
we all agree.

300
00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:43.425
we don't tell <i>anyone</i>
about Him. right?

301
00:17:45.631 --> 00:17:46.690
See you here tomorrow.

302
00:17:46.799 --> 00:17:47.799
- Shalom.

303
00:17:49.702 --> 00:17:50.795
♪♪

304
00:17:51.103 --> 00:17:52.571
(crickets chirping)

305
00:18:09.255 --> 00:18:12.384
♪♪

306
00:18:27.139 --> 00:18:28.334
JESUS:
Our Father.

307
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:29.500
KIDS:
Our Father.

308
00:18:29.609 --> 00:18:30.668
JESUS:
Who art in heaven.

309
00:18:30.776 --> 00:18:32.301
KIDS:
Who art in heaven.

310
00:18:32.411 --> 00:18:33.572
JESUS:
Hallowed be Thy name.

311
00:18:33.679 --> 00:18:35.204
- Hallowed be Thy name.

312
00:18:35.314 --> 00:18:36.407
- Thy kingdom come.

313
00:18:36.515 --> 00:18:38.279
- Thy kingdom come.

314
00:18:38.384 --> 00:18:39.818
- Thy will be done.

315
00:18:41.187 --> 00:18:43.122
♪♪

316
00:18:44.156 --> 00:18:45.556
(grinding noise)

317
00:18:47.493 --> 00:18:51.430
(woman vocalizing)

318
00:19:02.775 --> 00:19:04.539
JESUS: And laughing.
and nothing happened.

319
00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:06.613
And they thought they were safe.

320
00:19:06.712 --> 00:19:08.203
And all of a sudden.

321
00:19:08.314 --> 00:19:11.341
two she-bears
came out of nowhere.

322
00:19:11.450 --> 00:19:13.180
(roars)

323
00:19:13.285 --> 00:19:14.617
(giggling)

324
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:19.618
(women vocalizing)

325
00:19:34.774 --> 00:19:39.144
♪ - Behold how good
and how pleasing. ♪

326
00:19:39.245 --> 00:19:44.411
♪ - Behold how good
and how pleasing. ♪

327
00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:48.750
♪ - If brothers could
sit together in unity. ♪

328
00:19:48.854 --> 00:19:53.155
♪ - Brothers could
sit together in unity. ♪

329
00:19:53.259 --> 00:19:57.594
♪ - Behold how good
and how pleasing. ♪

330
00:19:57.697 --> 00:20:01.896
♪ - Behold how good
and how pleasing. ♪♪

331
00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:03.201
(wood clatters)

332
00:20:03.302 --> 00:20:05.271
(Children chattering)

333
00:20:12.945 --> 00:20:14.413
- So what did <i>you</i> do?

334
00:20:14.513 --> 00:20:16.812
- I tried to walk away.
but he wouldn't stop pushing me.

335
00:20:16.916 --> 00:20:20.512
So I pushed him so hard.
he fell down.

336
00:20:20.619 --> 00:20:22.645
- And that's why
you were punished.

337
00:20:22.755 --> 00:20:24.189
Did you expect
something different?

338
00:20:24.290 --> 00:20:25.815
- But even Torah says
"eye for eye."

339
00:20:25.925 --> 00:20:27.188
Why should I be punished too?

340
00:20:27.293 --> 00:20:29.285
- Yes. but that is for a judge.

341
00:20:29.395 --> 00:20:31.887
You were hardly
in a court of law.

342
00:20:31.997 --> 00:20:36.560
And you. all of you.
are to be special.

343
00:20:36.669 --> 00:20:39.264
You are to act differently
than others.

344
00:20:39.371 --> 00:20:43.433
- You tell us to be gentle.
but Rabbi Josiah

345
00:20:43.542 --> 00:20:46.706
said Messiah would lead us
against the Romans.

346
00:20:46.812 --> 00:20:49.907
that he would be
a great military leader.

347
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:53.845
- It is important
to respect your teachers

348
00:20:53.953 --> 00:20:58.687
and honor your parents.
and Rabbi Josiah is a smart man.

349
00:20:58.791 --> 00:21:03.695
But many times.
smart men lack wisdom.

350
00:21:03.796 --> 00:21:05.822
Is there anything in Scripture

351
00:21:05.931 --> 00:21:09.834
that says Messiah will be
a great military leader?

352
00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:11.597
There are many things
about Scripture

353
00:21:11.704 --> 00:21:15.664
that you cannot understand yet.
and that is okay. that is fine.

354
00:21:15.775 --> 00:21:18.370
You have many years
ahead of you.

355
00:21:18.477 --> 00:21:20.878
And God does not reveal
all things at once.

356
00:21:20.980 --> 00:21:24.439
But. children.
what if many of the things

357
00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:27.918
that our people think
about how we are to behave

358
00:21:28.020 --> 00:21:30.956
and how we are to treat
one another are wrong?

359
00:21:33.425 --> 00:21:35.257
You want things to be fair.

360
00:21:35.361 --> 00:21:38.422
When someone wrongs you.
you want to right it.

361
00:21:38.531 --> 00:21:39.965
And you know who else
loves justice?

362
00:21:43.869 --> 00:21:47.567
But what does the Lord say
in the law of Moses

363
00:21:47.673 --> 00:21:51.007
about justice and vengeance?

364
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:52.403
- "Vengeance is Mine."

365
00:21:52.511 --> 00:21:54.707
- Yes. very good. very good.

366
00:21:54.814 --> 00:21:56.715
Boys. pay attention.

367
00:21:56.816 --> 00:21:58.682
She doesn't even go
to Torah class. huh?

368
00:21:58.784 --> 00:22:00.446
(chuckles)

369
00:22:00.553 --> 00:22:02.852
The Lord loves justice.

370
00:22:02.955 --> 00:22:07.518
But maybe
it is not ours to handle.

371
00:22:07.626 --> 00:22:11.529
Do you remember when David had
the chance to kill King Saul.

372
00:22:11.630 --> 00:22:13.724
who was evil to him?

373
00:22:13.866 --> 00:22:14.925
But he didn't.

374
00:22:15.034 --> 00:22:18.300
Saul was God's anointed.

375
00:22:18.404 --> 00:22:21.533
And it was not
the right time for justice.

376
00:22:21.640 --> 00:22:24.872
And God says He will have
compassion on His people when.

377
00:22:24.977 --> 00:22:27.378
what?

378
00:22:27.479 --> 00:22:30.711
Let's see if someone who studies
this at school is learning. huh?

379
00:22:32.351 --> 00:22:33.876
- When their strength is gone?

380
00:22:33.986 --> 00:22:36.683
- Yes. very good.

381
00:22:36.789 --> 00:22:42.592
So. maybe we let <i>God</i>
provide the justice. hmm?

382
00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:45.665
Maybe we handle these things
in a different way.

383
00:22:45.764 --> 00:22:47.824
Not trying to be
the strongest all the time.

384
00:22:47.933 --> 00:22:49.367
- Even Messiah?

385
00:22:51.403 --> 00:22:53.429
- We will have to see.

386
00:22:53.539 --> 00:22:56.099
But do not expect Messiah
to arrive in Jerusalem

387
00:22:56.442 --> 00:23:00.470
on a tall horse.
carrying weapons.

388
00:23:00.579 --> 00:23:02.912
And He will be most pleased

389
00:23:03.015 --> 00:23:07.043
with those of you
who are the peacemakers.

390
00:23:07.152 --> 00:23:09.917
- Where were you yesterday?

391
00:23:10.022 --> 00:23:11.923
- I had to stay in town
later on.

392
00:23:12.024 --> 00:23:13.822
There was a woman
who needed My help.

393
00:23:13.926 --> 00:23:15.690
- Did you build something
for her?

394
00:23:15.794 --> 00:23:17.888
- No.

395
00:23:17.997 --> 00:23:20.489
You remember when I said
that I have a job

396
00:23:20.599 --> 00:23:23.831
that is bigger than My trade?

397
00:23:23.936 --> 00:23:28.499
There is a woman who has had
much pain in her life.

398
00:23:28.607 --> 00:23:30.667
and she was in trouble.

399
00:23:30.776 --> 00:23:31.776
So I helped her.

400
00:23:33.145 --> 00:23:34.511
- Is she your friend?

401
00:23:34.613 --> 00:23:35.842
- She is now.

402
00:23:35.948 --> 00:23:39.407
And I have chosen her.
and others.

403
00:23:39.551 --> 00:23:42.749
and more soon
to join me in traveling.

404
00:23:42.855 --> 00:23:44.619
- Do they know You?

405
00:23:44.723 --> 00:23:46.089
- Not yet.

406
00:23:46.191 --> 00:23:47.716
- But what if
they don't like You?

407
00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:49.920
(Jesus chuckles)

408
00:23:50.029 --> 00:23:52.396
- Many won't.

409
00:23:52.498 --> 00:23:54.126
This is my reason
for being here.

410
00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:55.513
- I still don't understand.

411
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:57.729
What <i>is</i> Your reason
for being here?

412
00:24:02.441 --> 00:24:04.433
- I'm telling you this.

413
00:24:04.543 --> 00:24:07.035
because even though
you are children.

414
00:24:07.146 --> 00:24:10.514
and the elders in your life
have lived longer.

415
00:24:10.616 --> 00:24:13.518
many times. adults need
the faith of children.

416
00:24:15.587 --> 00:24:22.426
And if you hold on
to this faith. really tightly.

417
00:24:22.561 --> 00:24:27.158
someday soon you will understand
all of what I am saying to you.

418
00:24:27.466 --> 00:24:29.697
But you ask
an important question. Abigail.

419
00:24:31.704 --> 00:24:33.172
What <i>is</i> My reason
for being here?

420
00:24:35.507 --> 00:24:37.635
And the answer
is for all of you.

421
00:24:42.748 --> 00:24:44.182
The Spirit of the Lord
is upon me.

422
00:24:46.685 --> 00:24:49.484
He has anointed Me to proclaim
good news to the poor.

423
00:24:52.024 --> 00:24:56.792
He has sent Me to proclaim
liberty to the captives.

424
00:24:56.895 --> 00:24:58.625
and recovering of sight
to the blind.

425
00:25:01.266 --> 00:25:04.498
To set at liberty
those who are oppressed.

426
00:25:06.205 --> 00:25:08.174
To proclaim the year
of the Lord's favor.

427
00:25:10.242 --> 00:25:11.870
- Isaiah.

428
00:25:14.847 --> 00:25:16.907
- Isaiah.

429
00:25:17.016 --> 00:25:19.508
I have loved
spending this time with you.

430
00:25:21.653 --> 00:25:23.246
You are all so very special.

431
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:30.155
And I hope that My next students
ask the same questions you do.

432
00:25:30.262 --> 00:25:31.924
and that they listen
to My answers.

433
00:25:35.601 --> 00:25:37.801
But I suspect they do not have
the understanding you do.

434
00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:45.739
And I hope that
when the time comes.

435
00:25:45.878 --> 00:25:49.007
they will tell others about Me.
like you have.

436
00:25:50.883 --> 00:25:56.849
♪♪

437
00:26:11.603 --> 00:26:12.901
(pounding)

438
00:26:15.808 --> 00:26:18.744
(pounding)

439
00:26:22.815 --> 00:26:23.976
(blows)

440
00:26:27.286 --> 00:26:30.279
(fire crackling)

441
00:27:01.153 --> 00:27:03.281
(birds chirping)

442
00:27:37.156 --> 00:27:40.354
- Abigail. I know you can read.

443
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:42.252
You are very special.

444
00:27:42.361 --> 00:27:44.023
This is for you.

445
00:27:44.129 --> 00:27:46.689
I did not come
only for the wealthy.

446
00:27:46.798 --> 00:27:51.634
♪♪

